This paper deals with intrusion detection in industrial control systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of statistical and machine learning based anomaly detection, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents a real-world industrial use case, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the use of network data and sensors, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
